Jane Doe,  \\n      \\n    Thank you for your application to the Software Engineer position at [Your Company]. We were impressed by your background and would like to invite you to a technical interview. Please choose one of the following slots that works best for you:  \\n      \\n      • Option A: Wednesday, March 10, 2024 at 10:00 AM PST  \\n      • Option B: Thursday, March 11, 2024 at 2:00 PM PST  \\n      \\n    The interview will be conducted via Zoom and last approximately 60 minutes. We will cover data structures, algorithms, and system design. You will receive a calendar invite once we confirm a slot.  \\n      \\n    Could you please confirm your preferred time by replying to this email by end of day tomorrow?  \\n      \\n    Thank you for your time, and we look forward to speaking with you.  \\n      \\n    Best regards,  \\n    [Your Name]  \\n    Talent Acquisition | [Your Company]  \\n    Email: recruiting@yourcompany.com  \\n    Phone: (123) 456-7890  \\n\\n2024-03-01 09:10  Step 3: Draft email to interviewers  \\n    To: eng-panel@yourcompany.com  \\n    Subject: Technical Interview Scheduled – Jane Doe  \\n    Body:  \\n    Dear Engineering Team,  \\n      \\n    We have invited Jane Doe to a technical interview for the Software Engineer role. Please review her resume and the job description attached.  \\n      \\n    Proposed Agenda (60 minutes total):  \\n      1. 10 min introductions  \\n      2. 20 min coding exercise (Algorithms) – Interviewer A  \\n      3. 20 min system design discussion – Interviewer B  \\n      4. 10 min Q&A and wrap-up – Interviewer A or B  \\n      \\n    Once Jane confirms her slot, I will send a calendar invite with the Zoom link. Please confirm your availability for both proposed slots by end of day tomorrow.  \\n      \\n    Thank you for your support.  \\n      \\n    Best regards,  \\n    [Your Name]  \\n    Talent Acquisition | [Your Company]  \\n\\n2024-03-01 09:15  Step 4: Send both emails via corporate email system  \\n    • Candidate email sent at 09:16 (Message ID: <cnd-20240301-0916>)  \\n    • Interviewers email sent at 09:17 (Message ID: <int-20240301-0917>)  \\n\\n2024-03-02 14:30  Step 5: Received responses  \\n    • Candidate (jane.doe@example.com) confirmed Option A (March 10, 10:00 AM PST) at 14:05 PST  \\n    • Interviewer A confirmed both slots at 11:00 PST  \\n    • Interviewer B confirmed both slots at 11:15 PST  \\n\\n2024-03-02 14:35  Step 6: Send confirmation emails  \\n\\n    6a. To Candidate:  \\n    To: jane.doe@example.com  \\n    Subject: Confirmation of Technical Interview – March 10, 2024  \\n    Body:  \\n    Dear Jane Doe,  \\n      \\n    Thank you for confirming. Your technical interview is scheduled for:  \\n      \\n      Date: Wednesday, March 10, 2024  \\n      Time: 10:00 AM – 11:00 AM PST  \\n      Zoom Link: https://yourcompany.zoom.us/j/123456789  \\n      Meeting ID: 123-456-789  \\n      Passcode: 987654  \\n      \\n    Please ensure you have a stable internet connection and a quiet environment. If you have any questions, let me know.  \\n      \\n    Best regards,  \\n    [Your Name]  \\n    Talent Acquisition | [Your Company]  \\n\\n    6b. To Interviewers:  \\n    To: eng-panel@yourcompany.com  \\n    Subject: Confirmed Interview – Jane Doe on March 10  \\n    Body:  \\n    Dear Team,  \\n      \\n    The technical interview with Jane Doe is confirmed:  \\n      \\n      Date: Wednesday, March 10, 2024  \\n      Time: 10:00 AM – 11:00 AM PST  \\n      Zoom Link: https://yourcompany.zoom.us/j/123456789  \\n      Meeting ID: 123-456-789  \\n      Passcode: 987654  \\n      \\n    Attached: Jane_Doe_Resume.pdf, Software_Engineer_JD.pdf  \\n      \\n    Agenda:  \\n      • 10:00–10:10 Introductions  \\n      • 10:10–10:30 Coding Exercise (Interviewer A)  \\n      • 10:30–10:50 System Design (Interviewer B)  \\n      • 10:50–11:00 Q&A & Wrap-up  \\n      \\n    Thank you for your time.  \\n      \\n    Best,  \\n    [Your Name]  \\n    Talent Acquisition | [Your Company]  \\n\\n2024-03-02 14:40  Step 7: Update ATS (Recruitment System)  \\n    • Candidate interview status: “Scheduled”  \\n    • Interview slot: 2024-03-10 10:00-11:00 PST  \\n    • Participants: Jane Doe, Interviewer A, Interviewer B  \\n    • Calendar invites sent  \\n\\n2024-03-08 10:00  Step 8: Send 2-day reminder  \\n    • To Candidate & Interviewers by email and calendar notification  \\n\\n2024-03-10 09:30  Step 9: Day-of preparation  \\n    • Verified Zoom link is active  \\n    • Confirmed Interviewers and candidate have connection details  \\n    • Standby in Zoom waiting room  \\n\\n---- end of workflow_log.txt ----\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:26:46,473", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_7\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Schedule the technical interview and send invitation emails to the candidate and interviewers\\n  Result: 1.  Compose email to candidate:\\n    *   Subject: Technical Interview Invitation\\n    *   Body:\\n        *   Express enthusiasm for candidate's application.\\n        *   Propose interview date and time options.\\n        *   Include details about the interview format (e.g., virtual, in-person).\\n        *   Specify topics to be covered in the interview.\\n        *   Request confirmation of availability.\\n        *   Thank the candidate for their time and consideration.\\n2.  Compose email to interviewers:\\n    *   Subject: Technical Interview - [Candidate Name]\\n    *   Body:\\n        *   Inform interviewers of the scheduled interview time and date.\\n        *   Provide the candidate's resume and job description for review.\\n        *   Outline the interview agenda and assigned responsibilities.\\n        *   Request confirmation of availability and preparation.\\n        *   Thank interviewers for their participation.\\n3.  Track email responses from candidate and interviewers.\\n4.  Upon confirmation from candidate and interviewers, send a confirmation email to both parties:\\n    *   To Candidate: Confirm the interview schedule and include any final instructions or resources.\\n    *   To Interviewers: Reiterate the schedule and attach the candidate's resume and job description.\\n5.  Update the recruitment system with the interview schedule and participant details.\\n6.  Two days before the interview, send a reminder email to both the candidate and the interviewers.\\n7.  On the interview day, ensure all parties have the necessary information and links (e.g., video conferencing link).\\n\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Generate a tailored set of technical interview questions based on job requirements and candidate profile\\n  Result: ```text\\n1. Analyze the job description to identify key technical skills and experience required.\\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume to identify their skills, experience, and qualifications.\\n3. Based on the job description and candidate's resume, create a list of technical interview questions covering:\\n    a. Python programming (e.g., data structures, algorithms, libraries like Pandas and NumPy)\\n    b. Data analysis and statistical modeling\\n    c. Machine learning algorithms and techniques\\n    d. SQL and database knowledge\\n    e. Data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, R)\\n    f. Experience with specific data science projects mentioned in the resume\\n4. Prepare follow-up questions to probe deeper into the candidate's understanding and problem-solving abilities.\\n5. Organize the interview questions in a logical order, starting with general questions and progressing to more specific and challenging questions.\\n6. Design coding exercises or problem-solving scenarios to assess the candidate's practical skills.\\n7. Define a scoring rubric for each question to evaluate the candidate's responses consistently.\\n8. Schedule the technical interview with the candidate.\\n9. Send a confirmation email to the candidate with interview details and any necessary instructions.\\n10. Conduct the technical interview, ask the prepared questions, and record the candidate's responses.\\n11. Score the candidate's responses based on the scoring rubric.\\n12. Send a thank you email to the candidate after the interview.\\n13. Document the interview process and candidate's performance.\\n14. Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses.\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Score the recorded interview responses using the extracted evaluation criteria\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nConduct the technical interview, present questions, and record candidate responses\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nJSON\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```txt\\n1. Prepare the interview environment (ensure stable internet connection, quiet room, necessary tools).\\n2. Greet the candidate and introduce yourself and the interview process.\\n3. Explain the structure of the interview (e.g., coding exercises, technical questions, Q&A).\\n4. Start with general technical questions to assess foundational knowledge.\\n5. Transition to specific questions related to Python, data analysis, machine learning, SQL, and data visualization, based on the prepared list of questions and the candidate's resume.\\n6. Present coding exercises or problem-solving scenarios to evaluate practical skills.\\n7. Ask follow-up questions to probe deeper into the candidate's understanding.\\n8. Encourage the candidate to explain their thought process and approach to problem-solving.\\n9. Record the candidate's responses to each question, noting the accuracy, clarity, and depth of their answers.\\n10. Observe the candidate's problem-solving skills, communication abilities, and overall demeanor.\\n11. Allow the candidate to ask questions about the role and the company.\\n12. Thank the candidate for their time and inform them about the next steps in the hiring process.\\n13. Conclude the interview and save the recorded responses for scoring.\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T17:26:46.473592\"\n}"}
