nterview time and date.\\n        *   Provide the candidate's resume and job description for review.\\n        *   Outline the interview agenda and assigned responsibilities.\\n        *   Request confirmation of availability and preparation.\\n        *   Thank interviewers for their participation.\\n3.  Track email responses from candidate and interviewers.\\n4.  Upon confirmation from candidate and interviewers, send a confirmation email to both parties:\\n    *   To Candidate: Confirm the interview schedule and include any final instructions or resources.\\n    *   To Interviewers: Reiterate the schedule and attach the candidate's resume and job description.\\n5.  Update the recruitment system with the interview schedule and participant details.\\n6.  Two days before the interview, send a reminder email to both the candidate and the interviewers.\\n7.  On the interview day, ensure all parties have the necessary information and links (e.g., video conferencing link).\\n\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Generate a tailored set of technical interview questions based on job requirements and candidate profile\\n  Result: ```text\\n1. Analyze the job description to identify key technical skills and experience required.\\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume to identify their skills, experience, and qualifications.\\n3. Based on the job description and candidate's resume, create a list of technical interview questions covering:\\n    a. Python programming (e.g., data structures, algorithms, libraries like Pandas and NumPy)\\n    b. Data analysis and statistical modeling\\n    c. Machine learning algorithms and techniques\\n    d. SQL and database knowledge\\n    e. Data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, R)\\n    f. Experience with specific data science projects mentioned in the resume\\n4. Prepare follow-up questions to probe deeper into the candidate's understanding and problem-solving abilities.\\n5. Organize the interview questions in a logical order, starting with general questions and progressing to more specific and challenging questions.\\n6. Design coding exercises or problem-solving scenarios to assess the candidate's practical skills.\\n7. Define a scoring rubric for each question to evaluate the candidate's responses consistently.\\n8. Schedule the technical interview with the candidate.\\n9. Send a confirmation email to the candidate with interview details and any necessary instructions.\\n10. Conduct the technical interview, ask the prepared questions, and record the candidate's responses.\\n11. Score the candidate's responses based on the scoring rubric.\\n12. Send a thank you email to the candidate after the interview.\\n13. Document the interview process and candidate's performance.\\n14. Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses.\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Score the recorded interview responses using the extracted evaluation criteria\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nConduct the technical interview, present questions, and record candidate responses\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nJSON\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interview_session\\\": {\\n    \\\"environment_prepared\\\": true,\\n    \\\"interviewer_greeting\\\": \\\"Hello, thank you for joining today. I am [Interviewer Name], and I will be conducting your technical interview.\\\",\\n    \\\"structure_explained\\\": \\\"We will begin with general technical questions, then move into domain-specific questions on Python, data analysis, machine learning, SQL, and data visualization, followed by a coding exercise and a Q&A.\\\",\\n    \\\"questions_and_responses\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": 1,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"General Technical\\\",\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between supervised and unsupervised learning. Provide examples of algorithms for each.\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Candidate’s response here.\\\",\\n        \\\"notes\\\": \\\"\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": 2,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Python\\\",\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe the use of decorators in Python. Can you provide an example?\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Candidate’s response here.\\\",\\n        \\\"notes\\\": \\\"\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Data Analysis\\\",\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"You're given a dataset with imbalanced classes. What techniques can you use to address this issue, and how would you evaluate their effectiveness?\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Candidate’s response here.\\\",\\n        \\\"notes\\\": \\\"\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Machine Learning\\\",\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain how you would approach feature selection for a high-dimensional dataset. What are some common methods, and what are their tradeoffs?\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Candidate’s response here.\\\",\\n        \\\"notes\\\": \\\"\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"SQL\\\",\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Given two tables, 'Orders' (OrderID, CustomerID, OrderDate) and 'Customers' (CustomerID, CustomerName, City), write an SQL query to list the CustomerName and OrderDate for all orders placed by customers from 'New York'.\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Candidate’s response here.\\\",\\n        \\\"notes\\\": \\\"\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": 6,\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Data Visualization\\\",\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe a scenario where you would use a box plot versus a histogram to visualize data.\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Candidate’s response here.\\\",\\n        \\\"notes\\\": \\\"\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\