{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:29:22,248", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Compile the scored r\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 4,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```text\\n1. Analyze Job Description: Review the job description to understand required skills, experience, and responsibilities.\\n2. Analyze Candidate Resume: Examine the candidate's resume to assess their qualifications, skills, and experience relevant to the job description.\\n3. Conduct Technical Interview: Perform a technical interview to evaluate the candidate's technical skills, problem-solving abilities, and communication skills.\\n4. Send Initial Interview Email: Send an email to the candidate confirming the interview schedule and providing any necessary instructions.\\n5. Send Follow-up Email (if needed): Send a follow-up email to the candidate to address any questions or concerns and provide reminders.\\n6. Score Candidate Responses: Evaluate the candidate's responses based on the defined scoring criteria and assign scores accordingly.\\n7. Compile Scores: Consolidate the scores for each evaluation category to calculate the total score.\\n8. Calculate Weighted Score: Multiply each category score by its corresponding weight and sum the weighted scores to obtain a weighted total score.\\n9. Generate Evaluation Report: Create a final evaluation report that includes the candidate's scores, comments, and overall assessment.\\n10. Total Raw Score Calculation: Sum of all 'score_awarded' values from the 'scores' list: 4 + 3 + 4 + 3 + 5 + 4 + 5 + 5 = 33.\\n11. Max Raw Score Calculation: Sum of all 'max_score' values multiplied by number of question in each category. For 'General Technical' is (5/5)*8 = 40.\\n12. Percentage Calculation:  (Total Raw Score / Max Raw Score) * 100 = (33/40) * 100 = 82.5%.\\n13. Weighted Score Calculation: (Category Weight * Score Awarded / Max Score). Sum this for all categories. (0.10 * 4/5) + (0.20 * 3/5) + (0.15 * 4/5) + (0.20 * 3/5) + (0.15 * 5/5) + (0.10 * 4/5) + (0.10 * 5/5) = 0.08 + 0.12 + 0.12 + 0.12 + 0.15 + 0.08 + 0.10 = 4.125.\\n14. Scale Weighted Score (Out of 5): Weighted Score = 4.125.\\n15. Document Observations: Record any relevant observations about the candidate's performance, strengths, and weaknesses.\\n16. Export Evaluation Report: Export the final evaluation report as a .txt file.\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\nThe current result only lists the steps without any actual content—no job‐descripti